title: Elon Musk's SpaceX suffers capsule anomaly during Florida tests
text: Elon Musk's SpaceX suffered an anomaly in one of its Crew Dragon capsules while conducting engine tests at the Cape Canaveral Air Force Station in Florida on Saturday, the company said.

title: This Reality Does Not Exist: Trust in an Age of Synthetic Media with Alexei Efros and Hany Farid
text: AI-based tools are proving capable of fabricating or modifying imagery and audio in ways that are nearly indistinguishable from reality. How can these systems and media be detected, and how can we trust anything when everything could be faked?

title: Fireside Chat with Anthony Levandowski (Pronto.AI)
text: Anthony Levandowski, the former star Google engineer and serial entrepreneur who was at the center of a trade secrets lawsuit between Uber and Waymo, is back with a new startup.

title: US intelligence reportedly says Huawei funded by Chinese state security

title: Weed supporters are celebrating this 420 as legalization gains momentum
text: Marijuana is now legal in 10 states and Washington, D.C. A handful of states are actively considering allowing adult recreational use.
